						<summary>

						<p>The inscription is much damaged. It seems to record an endowment in money deposited with two residents of the village, to provide for rice offering to god Bhuvani-Viṭaṅka (Naṭarāja) on his return to the temple after procession on the day of Tiruvādirai festival.</p>						

						</summary>
